@mcepl A rare word isa rare word. I don't know if hunspell supports it, doubt it. It gives you the ability to add a word like let's say wunderbar. I'd mark that rare, so I know, when I'm editing a normal document including German words, that that might be (and likely is) a typo. But it wasn't in one document where that was the part of a quote (i.e. sic).

Another use case of the ability to add rare words is you can add words like `pubic` as rare. I've done that LOL as I rarely want to write `pubic`, it's a typo from `public`. Again, a rare word.

You can also import whole dictionaries as rare. I have all of `~/.local/share/nvim/plugged/medical-spell-files/spell/medical_en` marked rare as it includes many acronyms that are probably typos.
